Global Rhabdomyolysis Treatment Market

Rhabdomyolysis treatment market is expected to gain market growth in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Data Bridge Market Research analyses the market is growing at a CAGR of 3.90% in the above-mentioned research forecast period. Rising geriatric population and increasing number of viral infections may drive the market growth.

Moreover, surge in awareness about disease cause and treatment and technological advancements also boost up the market growth. Moreover, increasing research and development and rising healthcare expenditure act as opportunities for the market growth. But, sometimes adverse effect related to the drugs, strict regulatory framework and lack of proper diagnostics facilities for diseases may hamper the rhabdomyolysis treatment market.

Rhabdomyolysis refers to the medical condition characterized by the rapid dissolution of injured or damaged skeletal muscle. Due to disruption of skeletal muscle integrity the direct release of intracellular components including creatine kinase, aldolase, muscle components, lactate dehydrogenase and electrolytes takes place directly into the blood stream and extracellular space. The Rhabdomyolysis condition ranges from an asymptomatic illness represented by the elevation in the creatine kinase level to a life-threatening condition recognized by the higher electrolyte imbalance, rise in the level of creatine kinase, acute renal failure and disseminated intravascular coagulation. The major cause associated with Rhabdomyolysis includes traumatic injury, moreover excessive consumption of toxins, drugs, infections, muscle ischemia, metabolic disorders, genetic disorders, exertion or prolonged bed-rest can also lead to Rhabdomyolysis. The patients suffers from Rhabdomyolysis relies on several treatment options including administration of intravenous (IV) fluids, mannitol, loop diuretics, dialysis treatment and surgery among others.

Rhabdomyolysis has been reported to adversely affect the males, obese people and people above the age of 60 years are more likely to develop this disease.

As per the data provided by the WHO the worldwide geriatric population over the age of 60 years expected to double from 12% to 22% in between the 2015 to 2050. This has been reported that patients above the age of 65 years have five time higher level of creatine kinase as compared to normal people, which is responsible for enhancing the cases of Rhabdomyolysis and hence expected to provide market with the lucrative growth. It is also estimated that Rhabdomyolysis treatment market is growing with the CAGR of 3.90% in 2020.

